Deconstructing graphics

  1. Scatter plot variables: exper, wage, sector, married role: exper on x-axis, wage on y-axis, color by married, faceted by sector

  2. Density plot variables: bmi, sex, pregnant role: bmi on x axis, color by sex, faceted by pregnant No data variable for y-axis because it is a density plot: measures number of cases on x-axis

ggplot(data = CPS85, aes(x =  exper, y = wage, color = married)) + geom_point() + facet_wrap( ~ sector)

ggplot(data = NCHS, aes(x = bmi, fill = TRUE, alpha = .01)) + geom_density(aes(color = sex)) + facet_wrap(~ pregnant)
